  "summary": "Benign install/import hook probe with loopback-only behavior",
  "details": "Package's setup.py overrides the install command to write a marker file to /tmp/pypi_install_hook_marker.txt and print a sentinel string. __init__.py attempts a loopback TCP connect to 127.0.0.1:1 (expected to fail) and prints additional markers. No remote network destinations, no credential or filesystem reads beyond the marker write, no execution of fetched code, no obfuscation. The behavior is self-documented in the README as a sandbox-probe package. While writing into /tmp at install time is an aggressive practice, the action is harmless to the installer and does not match any supply-chain attack class.",
